					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4688954">
																		Re: PF should use a more gradated rating system
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2893766&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226595" alt="Croquembouche" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2893766)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;" >Croquembouche</a></span> <span class="odate time_1592219517 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Jun 2020 11:11</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4688954">
									

<p>We'll be having a built-in no-vote option for sure.</p>
<p>Regarding the other vote options, I have a couple of problems with your reasoning:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This would promote a more critical userbase.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I suspect you might be thinking a little optimistically here.</p>
<p>Malicious downvoters, and anyone who thinks of a downvote as &quot;I don't want this on the site&quot;, will always pick -3. Malicious upvoters, and anyone who thinks of an upvote as &quot;this should stay on the site&quot;, will always pick +3.</p>
<p>Those who think critically will be picking their votes in the middle ranges, and therefore their opinions may literally count for less than those who think less critically. I don't think that's a mindset we want to encourage.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>reading an SCP I know is highly flawed but has a few elements that I find so interesting or compelling that I feel I must upvote it</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This situation comes entirely down to the preferences of the reader. You might upvote in that situation. Another person might see some good and some bad and cancel that out to a novote. Being able to adjust the intensity of your vote won't help you express a conflicted opinion, it just makes your vote weaker.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I simply cannot bring myself to downvote</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That's what the no-vote is there for (or rather, currently, a lack of any vote). The most useful thing you can do in this situation is leave a comment explaining your thoughts - a more nuanced rating system won't help the author. .</p>

							</div>

								
					
